<P><H1 align=center>CUSTOMER APPLICATION SUMMARY – CR030</H1>
<P></P>
<P><FONT color=red><STRONG>NOTE: </STRONG>fields shown in 
red are mandatory and must be completed to proceed</FONT>            </P>
<P><H3>Add: </H3>if the application is joint or a guarantor 
will be named, the second applicant and/or guarantor details need to be added. 
Clicking on ‘OK’ leads back to <A HREF="HELP_CR010.asp">Find Customer (CR010)</A>. If the details have 
previously been entered and the second applicant or guarantor already exists or 
has previously been deleted for an existing application, enter the search 
criteria and click on ‘Search’ to select the customer. If not, click on ‘New 
Customer’, which will allow the details to be entered. The <A HREF="HELP_CR020.asp">Customer Details 
screen (CR020)</A> should also be completed with the second applicant’s details
<P></P>
<P><H3>Edit: </H3>if any of the details entered and displayed 
in this summary were incorrect, highlight the record and click on ‘Edit’. This 
will lead back to <A HREF="HELP_CR020.asp">Customer Details (CR020)</A>, where the details can be amended, 
and then to <A HREF="HELP_CR025.asp">Customer Contact History (CR025)</A> where a note can be logged if the 
amendments have been made in response to customer contact
<P></P>
<P><H3>Delete: </H3>to delete a record, highlight it and click 
on ‘Delete’. The applicant will be deleted from the application, but will not be 
deleted from the system. Therefore if the applicant is deleted in error, click 
on ‘Add’ and search for the customer details that were entered previously on 
<A HREF="HELP_CR010.asp">Find Customer (CR010)</A>
<P></P>
<P><H3>Assign Applicants and Guarantors: </H3>this leads to 
<A HREF="HELP_CR050.asp">Assign Applicants / Guarantors (CR050)</A>
<P></P>
<P><H3>OK: </H3>this leads to the <A HREF="HELP_MN060.asp">Main Application Menu 
(MN060)</A>.
<P></P>

